BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Three foreigners were injured when a bomb exploded 
in front of the ticket office of the Ayasofya Museum in 
Istanbul. According to our correspondent, the bomb, which had 
earlier been planted in the garden of the Ayasofya Museum in 
Sultanahmet, exploded around 1200. Three persons who were near 
the ticket office -- one from Germany, one from Spain, and one 
from Netherlands -- were injured. The German woman is reported 
to be in serious condition. The injured were taken to Haseki 
and Istanbul Medical School Hospitals. Extensive searches are 
under way to catch the culprits. 

